

## Overview

Heart Rate Variability (HRV) has been shown to respond to geomagnetic disturbances, solar activity, and space weather events. This document summarizes key research findings on the relationship between solar/geomagnetic activity and cardiovascular autonomic regulation.

## Key Research Findings

### 1. Synchronization with Geomagnetic Activity

**McCraty et al. (2017)** - "Synchronization of Human Autonomic Nervous System Rhythms with Geomagnetic Activity in Human Subjects"
- **Journal**: International Journal of Environmental Research and Public Health
- **URL**: https://www.mdpi.com/1660-4601/14/7/770
- **Zotero Key**: XI6BYBEF

**Key Findings**:
- Continuous HRV monitoring over 31 days in 10 individuals identified coupling between geomagnetic activity and autonomic nervous system function
- Significant correlations found between HRV and:
  - Solar wind speed
  - Kp and Ap indices (geomagnetic activity)
  - Solar radio flux
  - Cosmic ray counts
  - Schumann resonance power
  - Total variations in magnetic field
- Time series analysis confirmed that participants' HRV rhythms synchronized with environmental magnetic variations

