### 3. Geomagnetic Disturbances Reduce HRV in Elderly Population

**Zilli Vieira et al. (2022)** - "Geomagnetic disturbances reduce heart rate variability in the Normative Aging Study"
- **Journal**: Science of the Total Environment
- **DOI**: 10.1016/j.scitotenv.2022.156144
- **URL**: https://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0048969722033320
- **Zotero Key**: DYCV3P2L

**Study Design**:
- 809 elderly men (mean age 74.5 ± 6.8 years)
- Normative Aging Study (Greater Boston Area)
- Repeated-measures mixed-effects regression models
- HRV outcomes: r-MSSD and SDNN

**Key Findings**:
- Intense geomagnetic activity up to 24 hours reduced HRV
- **Patients with coronary heart disease showed higher risk**
- Associations remained significant after adjusting for air pollutant exposures
- Geomagnetic activity may account for temporal HRV-related cardiovascular outcomes
- Circadian rhythm dysregulation linked to geomagnetic disturbances

